            . I am a <rs id="t18121202-28-viclabel157" type="occupation">sacking-manufacturer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18121202-28-victim324 t18121202-28-viclabel157"></join>, in <placeName id="t18121202-28-crimeloc158">Mark-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18121202-28-crimeloc158" type="placeName" value="Mark-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18121202-28-crimeloc158" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18121202-28-off155 t18121202-28-crimeloc158"></join>. On Tuesday morning last, as I was in my accompting-house; two or three of my men came in, and said, I had been robbed, and that the thief was taken in Hart-street. I immediately went these, and found the prisoner standing by a dozen of my sacks, which he had throwed down. I took him into my warehouse, and sent for an officer.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18121202-28-person326">
                  ABRAHAM 
                  CHAMBERS
               <interp inst="t18121202-28-person326" type="surname" value="CHAMBERS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18121202-28-person326" type="given" value="ABRAHAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18121202-28-person326" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was passing through my master's shop. I saw the prisoner looking over the sacks. I went up stairs, and put down the things that I had in my hand. I returned down stairs, and I saw the prisoner go out of the shop. I pursued him. He was taken with the sacks upon him. The twelve sacks are my master's property.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I leave it to your mercy.</p>
               <p>
